node.contents: If the nodes only point to their children, you'll need to keep track of each path on the way down. As mentioned in comment, you can do this with your own stack or with recursion. For example, you could always return find() call on the children of each node.

elements.contents: Boolean Search(Node node, String value, List<Node> track) { if (node == null) return false; if (node.data.equals(value)) { track.add(node); return true; } for(Node child : node.children) { if (Search(child, value, track) { track.insert(0, node); return true; } } return false; }
